<#
.SYNOPSIS
    GUI wrapper for Enable-TSxNestedHyperVVM.ps1 with remote and elevation support.
.DESCRIPTION
        Enable-TSxNestedHyperVVMUI provides a Windows Forms interface to connect to a
        Hyper-V host, select one or more virtual machines, and enable nested Hyper-V
        virtualization by calling Enable-TSxNestedHyperVVM.ps1.

        Connection modes:
            DCOM (default) - uses Hyper-V ComputerName / CIM DCOM sessions (legacy, no WinRM required).
            PSRemoting (WinRM) - uses New-PSSession / Invoke-Command; all Hyper-V commands run
                directly on the remote host. Enable the checkbox "Use PSRemoting (WinRM)" before connecting.

        Elevation:
            When the script is running as a standard (non-admin) user an "Elevate (Admin)" button
            is displayed at the bottom of the form. Clicking it relaunches the script elevated via
            UAC (Start-Process -Verb RunAs). Elevation is required for local Hyper-V access and for
            PSRemoting to the local host.

        Credentials:
            Click "Credential" to supply alternate credentials for remote connections.
            For local connections Hyper-V ignores supplied credentials; use the Elevate button instead.
.EXAMPLE
    .\Enable-TSxNestedHyperVVMUI.ps1
.NOTES
    FileName:    Enable-TSxNestedHyperVVMUI.ps1
    Author:      Mikael Nystrom
    Contact:     deploymentbunny@outlook.com
    Twitter:     @mikael_nystrom

    Disclaimer:
    This script is provided "AS IS" with no warranties, confers no rights and
    is not supported by the author.
.LINK
    https://www.deploymentbunny.com
#>

